<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1435,1317,1455]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,292,1317,1343]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Etymology.</emphasis>
From 
<emphasis box="[370,435,1317,1342]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">barys</emphasis>
(Gr. = heavy) + 
<emphasis box="[630,690,1317,1342]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">ilium</emphasis>
(L. = flank). In recognition of the massive (and heavy) build of the 
<typeStatus box="[194,297,1354,1380]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">holotype</typeStatus>
ilium and associated skeletal remains attributed to this taxon. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,474,1391,1417]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<typeStatus box="[197,258,1391,1417]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Type</typeStatus>
